If the base version is: 

{code}<p>A</p>{code}

And the left version is: 

{code}<p>A C</p><p></p>{code}

And the right version is: 

{code}<p>A D</p><p></p>{code}

The merge algorithm will not report a conflict but present the following as the merge result: 

{code}<p>A CA D</p><p></p>{code}

To make the merge work, the base version needs to be changed to: 

{code}<p>A B</p><p></p>{code}

Pasted this in the editor: aaa.bbb@domain.gov.au

Autoformatting does not work for the whole link 

*Update*: it works for {{aaa.bbb@domain.gov.au}} but it *doesn't* for {{Grace.Smith@sa.gov.au}}

